President Trump made remarks before departing for Arizona. He mentioned that over 200 miles of wall have been built on the border and that border crossings are at a record-breaking low. He also thanked law enforcement for stopping an attack on the Andrew Jackson monument in Lafayette Park. President Trump stated that those involved in vandalizing monuments will face long-term jail sentences. He mentioned plans for an executive order to reinforce protections for monuments. President Trump also stated that the federal government is willing to help states if they are unable to handle protests and riots. He addressed the high ratings of his recent rally in Oklahoma and defended his comments about slowing down testing for COVID-19, stating that the U.S. has the best testing program in the world. He emphasized that more tests result in more cases being discovered, but it also allows for better identification and treatment. President Trump claimed that the U.S. has the lowest mortality rate for COVID-19.